<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100817811015269></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100817811015269><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=6908&mid=100817811015269>RE: That nice warm feeling ...</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=6908&mid=100817811015269#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=123248><span id= >camabe</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>1 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Dec 12th 12:28 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm thrilled that I managed to get this weapon.  At lvl 28, a friend and I wandered over to Rathe Mountains to hunt skeles, not realizing the GM event was going on.  After promptly getting killed, we spent the next hour using her invis and my speed to drag corpses back to the zone.  A higher lvl group was letting folks loot their kills, and I was immensely greatful.  It definitely made dying and sticking around to help worthwhile.<br><br>I, too, have been getting skill increases with this weapon, though I see that some are saying that's either a bug or a fix.  I'm not sure... I do run noticeably faster (yes, geek that I am, I timed a few runs) when holding the weapon, but not nearly as fast as when I'm holding Mistmoore Drums (a gift from a guildmate for helping him out, and dying 11 times in the process).<br><br>This bard is my main (my SO and I have 3 accounts between us), and I've been playing for two years and just now about to hit lvl 31.  What can I say?  I get more out of the game by helping folks than by hunting things.<br><br>Linger<br>30 (almost 31st) Bar Bard<br>The Nameless<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
