<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100614083972032></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100614083972032><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=6908&mid=100614083972032>Testing Flameweaver with some songs</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=6908&mid=100614083972032#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=42795><span id=Sage>Daveon</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>20 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Nov 18th 10:33 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I tested a number of songs with Flameweaver to see if there were any benefits of holding the weapon while playing each type of song (ala the Singing Short Sword).  Quick summary:  Flameweaver does not increase the effectiveness of songs.<br><br>I tried with Chant of Battle (percussion), Hymn of Restoration (string), Crission's Pixie Strike (wind), Tuyen's Chant of Flame (percussion), and McVaxius Berserker Crescendo (brass), none of which benefitted from holding the weapon (ie, they were the same effectiveness as no instrument).  I also tried Melody of Ervaj (requires brass) and Shauri's Sonorous Clouding (requires wind), which would not play with the Flameweaver in either hand.<br><br>So it is still a bit of a mystery why I was able to get skill ups in two different brass songs (Appalling Screech and Berserker Crescendo), and a skill up in a string song (Hymn of Restoration), and others have reported percussion skill ups (my percussion is maxed at the moment, so I couldn't test it).  Normally, you can only get a skill up when holding the appropriate instrument.  So there's either SOMETHING special about the weapon, or there's a new bug to do with bard instrument skills.  Has anyone seen skill ups with weapons other than this weapon?<br><br>--Daveon Silverstring<br>--Brell Serilis<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
