this one.<br><br>I also wonder how many high level bards beat me to the flameweaver (before i finally beat them) only to put it in their bank.  Afterall, do we really want all the aggro that a 13 26 gives us?  or for that matter a 10 20 in the offhand?  I think an instrument would have been a much better drop for all bards.  the fact that these were weapons with identifyable stats, made them sexy for alternate characters.  People who don't truly appreciate bards would not have been too excited about some dumb lute, or some dumb horn :)<br><br>I bet the guys that got those nice weapons for their alternates are gonna level their bards like regular melee classes until the armor and weapons aren't good enough to overcome the fact that they are not playing the class the way it was meant to be played.  I would guess that happens in the low 30's.  If these had been instrument drops, those bards would be developing the way bards should :)<br><br>Byndala, I hope you managed to get both weapons.  Having scrapped your way to 45 you certainly deserve them!<br><br>Gladstone <br><br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
