	   <tr><td colspan=2>There's times when a bard wants aggro, like PLing or other maybe partnered with a priest of some sort. Times like this, I want to have my Di'Zok Wristsnapper in primary hand and my flameweaver in offhand. Other times, I want to avoid taunt, like in a full group with tanks. In these situations, I would go with the symphonic sabre in primary and wristsnapper in offhand.<br>Bards are flexible players and can take on many roles, even within a single group. That's why I carry 3 weapons (mentioned above) and assorted special-purpose gear around. I don't know from one encounter to the next what's going to be expected of me, but I never want to be without something critical. :)<br><br>Plugh MacMorrigan<br>Taleweaver of the 53rd stanza<br>Rodcet Nife<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
